cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.COM

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with transmission of information and uses orthogonal space-time block codes to increase reliability.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses transmission of system information in a cellular network.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper deals with transmission of information to inactive users in a cell.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as the paper discusses downlink transmission and precoding techniques in massive MIMO systems.
- cs.COM (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility as the paper involves analyzing the performance of different codes in various scenarios.
